"'''Love Never Felt So Good'''" is a song by American singer and songwriter [[Michael Jackson]], released posthumously on May 2, 2014. The song, reworked from a 1983 demo track originally composed by Jackson and Canadian singer-songwriter [[Paul Anka]], was the first single released from Jackson's second posthumous album, ''[[Xscape (album)|Xscape]]''. 

Two versions of the single were developed. The first was a solo version produced by American record producer John McClain and Dutch record producer [[Giorgio Tuinfort]]. The second version was a duet featuring American singer [[Justin Timberlake]], produced by American record producers [[Timbaland]] and [[Jerome "J-Roc" Harmon|J-Roc]], which received positive reviews from [[Music journalism|music critics]]. Its accompanying music video premiered on May 14, 2014 on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]''. In the video, Timberlake appears with a crowd of young dancers, who reference Jackson's most known dance moves, interspersed with archival footage of the pop singer's many short films. The song is the second collaboration between Jackson and Anka to be released since Jackson's death in 2009 — the first being "[[This Is It (Michael Jackson song)|This Is It]]".

The duet version of "Love Never Felt So Good" charted within the top ten in eighteen international charts, reaching the top spot in five countries. Michael Jackson became the first artist in history to have a top 10 single on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] in five different decades when "Love Never Felt So Good" reached number 9 on May 31, 2014 (six decades if his [[Jackson 5]] tenure is included). It spent eight weeks on top of the US Adult R&B Songs. The song also charted at number 8 on the [[UK Singles Chart]].

==Background==
First worked on as a demo, Jackson co-produced the song during a 1983 recording session with Anka. The original version only featured Jackson's vocals, finger snaps and a piano, played by Anka. In 1984, Anka sent the song to [[Johnny Mathis]], who recorded a new version of the song with revised lyrics by Anka and [[Kathleen Wakefield]].<ref name=history>{{cite news |url=http://www.showbiz411.com/2014/05/01/michael-jackson-new-single-written-with-paul-anka-is-actually-31-years-old |title=Michael Jackson 'New' Single Written with Paul Anka Is Actually 31 Years Old |work=Showbiz411.com |date=May 1, 2014 |accessdate=May 2, 2014}}</ref> Mathis' version made it on his 1984 album, ''[[A Special Part of Me]]''. In 2006, Jackson's demo leaked online. During the 2013-2014 recording sessions for the ''Xscape'' album, the song was given a revision as a disco-sounding track. The first version, which only features Jackson, was produced by John McClain and Giorgio Tuinfort and was featured as the first track on the standard version of ''Xscape''. The second version, featured as the last track on the deluxe version of the album, was co-produced by Timbaland and J-Roc and featured Timberlake in duet vocals with Jackson. While producing Timberlake's duet version, Timberlake sampled the percussion and breaths from Jackson's 1979 song "[[Workin' Day and Night]]".

==Release==
On April 30, 2014, it was revealed that "Love Never Felt So Good" would be unveiled at the [[iHeartRadio Music Awards]] on May 1, 2014 as the album's first single. During the awards show, the song premiered with a tribute by American R&B singer [[Usher (entertainer)|Usher]].<ref name=RollingStone>{{cite web |title=Michael Jackson's New Single to Premiere at iHeart Radio Music Awards |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/michael-jacksons-new-single-to-premiere-at-iheartradio-music-awards-20140501 |first=Jon |last=Blistein |date=May 1, 2014 |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |accessdate=May 1, 2014}}</ref> The digital download for the single became available on [[iTunes]] at 0:01 [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]] on May 2, 2014 on both its album version and duet version with [[Justin Timberlake]].<ref name=Revealed>{{cite web |title=XSCAPE Deluxe Edition Tracklisting Revealed! |url=http://www.michaeljackson.com/us/news/xscape-deluxe-edition-tracklist-contents-announced |date=May 1, 2014 |work=michaeljackson.com |accessdate=May 1, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140713214652/http://www.michaeljackson.com/us/news/xscape-deluxe-edition-tracklist-contents-announced |archive-date=July 13, 2014 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/michael-jacksons-love-never-felt-so-good-first-single-from-xscape-premieres-tonight-at-the-iheart-radio-music-awards-257596061.html|title=Michael Jackson's "Love Never Felt So Good" First Single From XSCAPE Premieres Tonight at the iHeart Radio Music Awards|date=May 1, 2014 |accessdate=May 1, 2014 |work=Epic Records |publisher=PR Newswire}}</ref> The release date of the single to urban radio stations was confirmed as May 6, 2014, though actually the single hit the radios on May 2.<ref name=debutsingledate>{{cite web|url=http://www.allaccess.com/urban/future-releases|title=Urban/UAC Future Releases - R&B, Hip Hop, Release Schedule and Street Dates|date=May 2, 2014 |accessdate=May 2, 2014 |publisher=All Access |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6PG47r6Qv?url=http://www.allaccess.com/urban/future-releases |archivedate=May 2, 2014}}</ref> On May 10, 2014 a [[Fedde Le Grand]] remix was announced and world-premiered by [[Danny Howard]] on his [[BBC Radio 1]] show ''Dance Anthems''. The remix was released on May 19, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|last=Le Grand|first=Fedde|title=Michael Jackson - Love Never Felt So Good (Fedde Le Grand remix) (Danny Howard BBC Radio 1 premiere)|url=https://soundcloud.com/feddelegrand/mj-lnfsg-flgrmx|work=BBC Radio 1|publisher=Soundcloud|accessdate=10 May 2014}}</ref>

== Critical reception ==
Upon its release, "Love Never Felt So Good" received positive reviews from critics. Surprised by the quality of the song, Aisha Harris from ''Slate'' magazine wrote that Timberlake's version "sounds like an outtake from ''[[Off the Wall (album)|Off the Wall]]''" and further commented: "If producers are going to put out more MJ music, let's hope it continues to sound this good."<ref name=Slate>{{cite web |title=The New Michael Jackson Song With Justin Timberlake is Actually Good|url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/browbeat/2014/05/02/new_michael_jackson_song_with_justin_timberlake_listen_to_love_never_felt.html |date=May 2, 2014 |publisher=Slate |accessdate=May 2, 2014}}</ref> Carl Willott of [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] offered a positive outlook on the duet version, stating: "... where [Timberlake and Jackson's] voices make for an uncannily natural combination ... the other great thing is that it's not trying to be an event, it's just a breezy dance floor strut that wouldn't feel out of place on ''Off the Wall'' or ''[[The 20/20 Experience]]''."<ref name="autogenerated1">{{cite web |title=Michael Jackson & Justin Timberlake's "Love Never Felt So Good": Listen |url=http://www.idolator.com/7516769/michael-jackson-justin-timberlake-love-never-felt-so-good |date=May 2, 2014 |publisher=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |accessdate=May 2, 2014}}</ref> 

Chris Richards of ''[[The Washington Post]]'' called the solo Jackson rendition "terrific. It's airy, sweet, funky and pretty much impossible to dislike," but panned the Timberlake remix, which he commented "surfaces all the grody feelings that came rushing in 2010 with Jackson's first posthumous album, ''[[Michael (album)|Michael]]''."<ref>{{cite web |title=Michael Jackson, "Love Never Felt So Good" - it's trending, but is it good?|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/style-blog/wp/2014/05/02/michael-jackson-love-never-felt-so-good-its-trending-but-is-it-good/ |date=May 2, 2014 |publisher=Washington Post |accessdate=May 2, 2014}}</ref> Gavin Edwards from ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' said, "even if it isn't on a par with Jackson's best work, it sounded like it could have easily been the sixth single off ''[[Bad (album)|Bad]]'', which is more impressive than it sounds."<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/iheartradio-music-awards-2014s-10-best-and-worst-moments-20140502 | title=IHeartRadio Music Awards 2014's 10 Best and Worst Moments | publisher=[[Jann Wenner]] | work=[[Rolling Stone]] | date=May 2, 2014 | accessdate=May 4, 2014 | first=Gavin |last=Edwards}}</ref>
Stephanie Chase from ''Contactmusic'' said that "It's not groundbreaking or an exceptional example of his artistry, but it gives a good indication that ''[[Xscape (album)|Xscape]]'' could serve as a fitting tribute to Jackson and his legacy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/single-review/michael-jackson-love-never-felt-so-good|title=Michael Jackson - Love Never Felt So Good Single Review - Contactmusic.com|author=Stephanie Chase|work=Contactmusic.com}}</ref> Jon O'Brien from [[Yahoo!]] commented: "the classy disco-soul of this single could easily have been lifted from ''Off the Wall'' or ''[[Thriller (Michael Jackson album)|Thriller]]''."<ref>{{cite web | url=https://uk.celebrity.yahoo.com/news/weekly-singles-review-michael-jackson-ft-justin-timberlake-105400349.html | title=Weekly Singles Review: Michael Jackson ft. Justin Timberlake, Foxes & Pitbull | publisher=Yahoo! | date=May 5, 2014 | accessdate=May 5, 2014 | first=Jon | last=OBrien | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140505182949/https://uk.celebrity.yahoo.com/news/weekly-singles-review-michael-jackson-ft-justin-timberlake-105400349.html | archive-date=2014-05-05 | dead-url=yes | df= }}</ref>

"Love Never Felt So Good" also got praised by musician [[DJ Cassidy]], who told the song had a positive impact on him.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/3233122|title=Michael Jackson – Love Never Felt So Good Lyrics - Genius Lyrics|work=Genius}}</ref>

<blockquote>I haven't been a huge fan of albums that come out after an artist dies. You know, it just doesn't have their stamp on it, so it's never going to be what it would have been if the person was alive. But "Love Never Felt So Good" was a great record. It was definitely one of my top five songs from the last five years.</blockquote>

==Commercial performance==
[[File:Justin_Timberlake_Cannes_2013.jpg|thumb|right|170px|"Love Never Felt So Good" became Michael Jackson's 29th top-ten single and Justin Timberlake's ''(pictured)'' 16th on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]].<ref name=":0" />]]
The single debuted on the [[UK Singles Chart]] at No. 27 in the issue dated May 4, 2014 after just 24 hours on sale.<ref name="bbc_debut">{{cite news | url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment_and_arts/ | title=Calvin Harris scores sixth UK number one | work=BBC | date=May 4, 2014 | accessdate=May 5, 2014 | location=London, England}}</ref><ref name="ukchartreview">{{cite web | url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/calvin-harris-scores-his-sixth-uk-number-1-single-with-summer-2980/ | title=Calvin Harris scores his sixth UK Number 1 single with Summer | work=officialcharts.com | publisher=[[Official Charts Company]] | date=May 4, 2014 | accessdate=May 5, 2014 | first=Daniel |last=Lane}}</ref> It reached number one in South Korea, Denmark, Israel, South Africa, and Germany and Belgium's respective urban charts.

In the United States, the single sold more than 90,000 downloads from the debut date of May 2, 2014 to May 4, 2014, and drew 52 million all-format radio audience impressions since its first plays that Friday. With the [[Clear Channel]]'s promotional synergy after the premiere of the song on the [[iHeartRadio Music Awards]], the song received hourly plays on May 2, 2014 on the company's pop, adult and R&B/hip-hop stations, greatly contributing to its airplay,<ref name="bbdebut">{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6077508/michael-jackson-justin-timberlake-hot-100-love-never-felt-so-good | title=Michael Jackson, Justin Timberlake's Duet Off To More Than 'Good' Start | work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | date=May 5, 2014 | accessdate=May 6, 2014 | first1=Gary |last1=Trust |first2=Keith |last2=Caulfield}}</ref> which made the song debut on the following ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' radio charts: Adult R&B Songs (No. 1), Adult Contemporary (No. 2), R&B/Hip-Hop Airplay (No.  4) and Adult Pop Songs (No.  21).<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6077518/chart-highlights-beyonce-scores-20th-dance-club-songs-no-1-with | title=Chart Highlights: Beyonce Scores 20th Dance Club Songs No. 1 With 'Partition' | work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | date=May 5, 2014 | accessdate=May 6, 2014 | first=Gary |last=Trust}}</ref> The song made splashy debuts at No. 20 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6092276/michael-jackson-coldplay-hot-100-top-10-john-legend-no-1 |title=Michael Jackson, Coldplay Hit Hot 100 Top 10; John Legend Still No. 1 |publisher=Billboard |date= |accessdate=2014-08-14}}</ref> and No. 6 on ''Billboard'' [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] from 80,000 downloads sold, 34 million audience impressions from 358 radio stations, and 1.9 million U.S. streams, which made it Jackson's highest-charting entry since the 2002 single "[[Butterflies (Michael Jackson song)|Butterflies]]".<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6077659/michael-jackson-justin-timberlake-love-never-felt-so-good-hot-100-charts | title=Michael Jackson, Justin Timberlake Storm Onto Hot 100, Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs Charts | work=Billboard.com | publisher=Prometheus Global Media | date=7 May 2014 | accessdate=8 May 2014 | author=Keith Caulfield & Gary Trust}}</ref>
After its first full week on sale, the song reached No. 6 on ''Billboard'''s [[Digital Songs]] chart with sales of 101,000 copies, but the whole week radio audience impressions reduced 36% to 22 million which caused the song to drop to No. 38 on [[Hot 100 Airplay|Radio Songs]], and lowered the song's Hot 100 position to #22 in its second week on the chart.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/chart-alert/6084904/now-50-bumps-frozen-from-no-1-on-billboard-200 | title='Now 50' Bumps 'Frozen' From No. 1 On Billboard 200 | work=Billboard.com | publisher=Prometheus Global Media | date=14 May 2014 | accessdate=15 May 2014 | author=Keith Caulfield}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/chart-alert/6091993/chart-moves-jason-derulo-wiggles-up-hot-100-black-keys-unlock | title=Chart Moves: Jason Derulo 'Wiggle's Up Hot 100; Black Keys Unlock Alternative No. 1; Jamiroquai Jams Back Onto Dance Charts | work=Billboard.biz | publisher=Prometheus Global Media| date=16 May 2014 | accessdate=18 May 2014 | author=Gary Trust}}</ref> In its third week, the song rose to No. 9, becoming Jackson's first top-ten hit since 2001's "[[You Rock My World]]".<ref name=":0">{{cite web|url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6092276/michael-jackson-coldplay-hot-100-top-10-john-legend-no-1|title = Michael Jackson, Coldplay Hit Hot 100's Top 10; John Legend Still No. 1|date = May 21, 2014|accessdate = May 21, 2014|website = Billboard.com|publisher = |last = Trust|first = Gary}}</ref> Jackson also became the first act in the Hot 100's history to score top ten hits in five different decades, as he has done for each decade from the 1970s to the 2010s.<ref name=":0" /> The single then topped the US ''Billboard'' Top Adult R&B Songs chart for 8 weeks.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6221820/chart-highlights-sam-smiths-stay-hits-no-1-on-pop-songs | title=Chart Highlights: Sam Smith's 'Stay' Hits No. 1 On Pop Songs | work=Billboard | date=August 18, 2014 | accessdate=April 25, 2016 | author=Trust, Gary}}</ref> "Love Never Felt So Good" has since been certified platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA). As of 2018, the song has sold 1.11 million copies in the country.<ref name="us sales">{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8097976/justin-timberlake-nsync-career-album-song-sales-ask-billboard|title=Ask Billboard: Justin Timberlake & *NSYNC's Career Album & Song Sales |work=Billboard |publisher=Billboard-Hollywood Media Group |date=February 4, 2018 |accessdate=February 4, 2018 |last=Trust |first=Gary}}</ref>

Counting Jackson's entire chart career in addition to his solo career, the 2010s is actually his sixth decade with a single charted (not peaking) in the US Top 10, as [[The Jackson 5]] single "[[I Want You Back]]" first reached the Top 10 the week of December 27, 1969, on its way to a number one peak in late January 1970; however, Jackson was not credited on that single as an individual artist.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/1969-12-27/hot-100 | title=The Hot 100: Dec. 27, 1969 | work=Billboard.com | publisher=Prometheus Global Media | accessdate=21 May 2014 | author=Billboard}}</ref>

In 2014, "Love Never Felt So Good" was ranked as the 78th most popular song of the year (2014) on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2014/hot-100-songs|title=2014 Year End Charts - Hot 100 Songs|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=December 9, 2014}}</ref>

==Music videos==
The music video for the duet debuted in the morning on May 14, 2014, which was regarded as "a careful visual tribute of the late pop singer's lasting legacy on future generations." It was directed by [[Rich Lee]] and [[Justin Timberlake]].<ref>{{cite web|author=05/14/2014 |url=http://rapdose.com/2014/05/14/michael-jackson-love-never-felt-so-good-feat-justin-timberlake-official-music-video |title=Michael Jackson – Love Never Felt So Good (Feat. Justin Timberlake) (Official Music Video) |publisher=Rap Dose |date=2014-05-14 |accessdate=2014-08-14}}</ref> A crowd of young dancers lip synced and Justin Timberlake sang along and made some memorable moves from Michael Jackson's classic music videos or live shows. Clips from the following music videos appeared in the "Love Never Felt So Good" music video (in order of appearance):<ref name="MVDEBUG">{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6084922/michael-jackson-justin-timberlake-love-never-felt-so-good-video | title=Michael Jackson & Justin Timberlake's 'Love Never Felt So Good' Video Premieres | work=Billboard.com | publisher=Prometheus Global Media | date=14 May 2014 | accessdate=15 May 2014 | author=Ashley Lee}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/earshot/video-love-never-felt-good-705184 | title=17 Iconic Michael Jackson Shots in 'Love Never Felt So Good' with Justin Timberlake (Video) | work= The Hollywood Reporter | publisher=Prometheus Global Media | date=17 May 2014 | accessdate=18 May 2014 | author=Ashley Lee}}</ref>

