A month later, a music video for the solo version was uploaded to the official Michael Jackson YouTube channel. The music video featured clips from the duet version, as well as clips from other Michael Jackson music videos, such as "[[Dirty Diana]]" and "[[You Rock My World]]", along with some of Jackson's live performances, such as "Billie Jean".<ref name="solomv">{{cite web | url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2014/06/19/michael-jackson-love-never-felt-so-good-video-premiere/10884299/ | title=Premiere: New Michael Jackson video | publisher=USAToday.com | work=[[USA Today]] | date=19 June 2014 | accessdate=21 June 2014 | author=Brian Mansfield,}}</ref>

==Live performance==
The song was performed live at the 2014 [[iHeart Radio]] Music Awards on May 1, 2014.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-juice/6077187/michael-jackson-justin-timberlake-duet-love-never-felt-so-good | title=Michael Jackson & Justin Timberlake Duet 'Love Never Felt So Good' Arrives Online: Listen | work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | date=May 2, 2014 | accessdate=May 3, 2014}}</ref> American R&B singer [[Usher (entertainer)|Usher]] danced across the stage, moonwalked, and hopped on a table to spin during the play of the song. Other dancers dressed in Jackson's style performed his signature moves in front of digital backdrops flashing graffiti and brick walls.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://music.yahoo.com/blogs/music-news/usher-channels-michael-jackson-for--love-never-felt-so-good--preview-025947261.html | title=Usher Channels Michael Jackson for 'Love Never Felt So Good' Preview | publisher=Yahoo Music | work=Yahoo Music | date=May 2, 2014 | accessdate=May 3, 2014 | first=Billy |last=Johnson, Jr.}}</ref>

